### OmniVoice API requests
### Works best with JetBrains HTTP Client or VS Code REST Client.
### Start the server first:
### .venv/bin/python -m omnivoice.cli.api_server --model k2-fsa/OmniVoice --ip 0.0.0.0 --port 8002

@host = http://127.0.0.1:8002
@ref_audio_path = ./ref.wav

### Health
GET {{host}}/health
Accept: application/json

###

### Languages
GET {{host}}/languages
Accept: application/json

###

### Auto mode
POST {{host}}/generate
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=OmniVoiceBoundary

--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="mode"

auto
--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="text"

Hello from the OmniVoice API.
--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="num_step"

16
--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="guidance_scale"

2.0
--OmniVoiceBoundary--

###

### Design mode
POST {{host}}/generate
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=OmniVoiceBoundary

--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="mode"

design
--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="text"

This voice was designed through the API request file.
--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="instruct"

female, low pitch, british accent
--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="num_step"

32
--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="guidance_scale"

2.0
--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="postprocess_output"

true
--OmniVoiceBoundary--

###

### Clone mode
### Update @ref_audio_path to point at a real local WAV file before sending.
### Many HTTP clients support `< ./file.wav` for file inclusion in multipart requests.
POST {{host}}/generate
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=OmniVoiceBoundary

--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="mode"

clone
--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="text"

This request tests zero-shot voice cloning over HTTP.
--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="ref_text"

This is the transcript of the reference audio.
--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="num_step"

32
--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="guidance_scale"

2.0
--OmniVoiceBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="ref_audio"; filename="ref.wav"
Content-Type: audio/wav

< {{ref_audio_path}}
--OmniVoiceBoundary--

###

### Notes
### Inspect these response headers after each request:
### X-OmniVoice-Request-Id
### X-OmniVoice-Started-At
### X-OmniVoice-Finished-At
### X-OmniVoice-Latency-Ms
### X-OmniVoice-Audio-Duration-S
### X-OmniVoice-RTF
